[thinking] **Evaluating socket appender functionality**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering the use of SocketHubAppender for public access and whether that's necessary. It seems the ServerMonitor is set up to handle the run/sendCachedEvents correctly, which is good. I’m weighing the idea that dynamic access might relate to ObjectOutputStream#writeObject in the sendCachedEvents process. Since this call occurs on the server thread, I wonder if it maps effectively to that thread. It appears fine for now, though!
[thinking] 
